rComments: Great prof who teaches the material well and makes it interesting. Easy to talk to and get feedback from, and the essays are marked fairly and you are given plenty of time to work on them. Don't forget to do the weekly quizzes!
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Amazing lectures', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Michael Raby is an excellent professor. His lectures were both stimulating and engaging. He uses video/audio clips and current events to keep things interesting. His teaching motivates you to keep up with the readings and he provides helpful advice for essay writing during office hours. The exam is also fairly easy.

Such an awesome experience in this class! Dr. Raby is extremely engaging during lectures and the content he covers in class is worth being there for; keep up with the readings and use his office hours, hes super helpful with the essays and readings if you dont understand something.

His lectures are filled with knowledge and beautiful information. He is easy to talk to in office hours, and if you have class, he will take out time to make sure you are able to see him! He tries to make sure his students take the most out of this course. His assignments are not there to test your intelligence, rather help you learn and progress.

Professor Raby introduced me to the beauty of English literature, and for that I will always in debt to him. He's super chill, and really cool to talk with during office hours. He cares about his students, and the material.. so, good for you if you are taking him.
Really chill even though he has a monotone voice. Didn't really enjoy the class content but when I went to see him in office hours, he's helpful, understanding, and nice. Cool guy.
He's super intelligent and makes class so relateable. He played Monty Python and Rick and Morty clips in class to help us understand concepts. You can't really get better than that.
